-- VTB, RusHydro, Polymetal, Lukoil May Move: Russia Equity Market Preview
-- B y   M a r i a   K o l e s n i k o v a
-- 2010-11-01T04:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/vtb-rushydro-polymetal-lukoil-may-move-russia-equity-market-preview.html
The following shares may have unusual
price changes in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are from the previous close unless
otherwise noted.  The 30-stock  Micex Index  rose 1.1 percent to 1,523.39, the
biggest gain since Oct. 21 and a 5.8 percent advance in the
month. The dollar-denominated  RTS Index  gained 0.2 percent to
1,587.14.  VTB Group  (VTBR RX): Russia’s second-biggest lender signed
an agreement with Bank for Investment and Development of Vietnam
to set up a joint $500 million fund for investing in energy and
mining, VTB Chief Executive Officer Andrei Kostin told reporters
Oct. 31. VTB rose 1.2 percent to 10.13 kopeks in Moscow.  OAO RusHydro  (HYDR RX): Russia’s biggest renewable energy
company signed a preliminary agreement with Vietnam Oil & Gas
Group, known as PetroVietnam, to build a hydro-power plant in
Vietnam and said it is targeting projects in Southeast Asia for
expansion. RusHydro rose 0.1 percent to 1.585 rubles.  OAO Polymetal  (PMTL RX): Gold rose, capping a third
straight monthly gain, on speculation that the Federal Reserve
will increase debt purchases, weakening the dollar and boosting
the metal’s appeal as an alternative investment. Silver also
gained. Russia’s biggest silver producer dropped 1.6 percent to
493.62 rubles.  OAO Lukoil  (LKOH RX): Crude oil fell in New York, paring
monthly gain, and may decline this week as U.S. stockpiles
increase, threatening to form a glut in the world’s biggest oil-
consuming nation. Russia’s largest non-state oil producer gained
1 percent to 1,726.76 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Maria Kolesnikova  in Moscow at 
 mkolesnikova@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net . 